How to connect POS to your business with Wix

Follow these 6 steps to connect Wix POS. Wix Point of Sale is currently available to users based in the U.S., Canada and U.K. (except Northern Ireland) who are connected to Wix Payments. To receive payouts from Wix, complete your Wix
Payments verification.

Talk to Sales
Shop POS

01

Get started with Wix 

Log in or create an account to set up your business website. Choose a Wix Premium plan to suit your business.

02

Set up Wix Payments

Connect Wix Payments in your payments settings. When onboarding, make sure to select POS as a payment method and check that your business type is supported.

03

Buy your POS system

Find the right Wix Point of Sale system for your business by browsing our POS Shop. Choose the hardware that suits your business best.

04

Get a POS Plan

To accept payments via credit card and digital wallets with Wix POS Register, you need to buy the Wix Retail POS Pro plan. There is no POS plan needed if you’re just using Mobile POS.

05

Set up Wix POS

We’ll ship your POS hardware to you. Everything you need is built in, including our advanced Wix POS software. Simply unbox your POS system and plug it in.

06

Start selling

You’re now all set to accept in-person payments. Log in to your Wix account on a POS tablet, computer or Wix app and you’re good to go.

POS system FAQ

What is a POS (point of sale)?

POS is a system that allows you to accept payments from your customers when they are making a purchase. Wix POS offers multiple combinations of POS hardware and software, ranging from our POS Register to our compact Mobile Card Reader that connects to our mobile app. Therefore, you get full freedom to manage your business by selecting a POS system tailored to you.

Which POS system should I choose for my business?

This is up to you, we offer Point of Sale solutions for different business needs whether you sell in store, in your salon, gym or on the go. To sell in your retail store, choose our POS Register or POS Go, and add POS accessories as you grow your business.


If you sell on the move, the Wix Mobile POS package allows you to accept payments wherever you like, whether you’re selling at events, markets, sessions, pop-ups, classes or more. The Wix POS Go is also an ideal solution if you need to charge customers for bookings and orders right from your laptop or computer, but also want the option to charge on the go.

What should I consider when choosing a POS system? ​​

There are a few factors you need to consider when picking a point of sale for your business. You should consider a POS system which not only lets you accept payments but also helps you manage your business too. Other factors to consider when selecting a POS:

  • Hardware type, e.g. Register POS or simply Mobile POS

  • Easy-to-use hardware and software

  • Integration with other software and apps

  • PCI compliance

  • Costs, e.g. POS packages and pricing plans

How can I order Wix POS hardware?

Once you’re connected to Wix Payments, visit our POS Shop directly or from your Wix dashboard (U.S., Canada and U.K.-based (except Northern Ireland)) to find the right POS system for your business. When we get your order, we’ll ship your hardware and send you a tracking number.


For more info on Wix POS hardware, book a call with a Wix POS Expert.

What is included in Wix POS hardware?

When buying POS hardware, the software is already included. All our POS kits have Wix POS software built in, meaning you won’t be charged any additional fees for software. To accept payments on Wix, you need to get a supporting premium plan, so if you haven’t already purchased one, choose the plan that suits your business best. Once you start taking in-person payments, you’ll pay a fixed processing fee.

Can I use any POS hardware with Wix POS?

Currently, only devices listed in our Wix Point of Sale Shop are supported.

What payment options are available with Wix POS?

Wix Point of Sale is supported by our own payment solution, Wix Payments, so you get to enjoy all the perks of our payment solution. At checkout, you can accept all leading debit/credit cards (including chip, classic magstripe and contactless NFC cards), plus digital wallets like Apple Pay, Google Pay and more. Note, you’re also able to accept cash and gift cards as payment.

What do I need to pay for when I purchase a Wix POS system?

First, you’ll pay for the Wix POS hardware you order. All our POS kits have Wix POS software built in, meaning you won’t be charged any additional fees for software. To accept payments on Wix, you need to get an active Wix Premium plan that supports payments, so if you haven’t already purchased one, choose the plan that fits you most. Additionally, POS Register users need to buy the Wix Retail POS Pro plan to accept payments from debit/credit cards, digital wallets and more. Note, once you start taking in-person payments, you’ll need to pay a fixed processing fee per transaction.

What will happen if my Wix Premium plan is expired or canceled?

If your Wix Premium plan is no longer valid, you won’t be able to accept payments with Wix POS. If this happens, you will need to renew your premium plan to resume taking payments again.

How long will it take to set up my point of sale?

After your hardware arrives, it should take between 5-7 days to complete the entire setup. Once you receive it, just follow these steps to have your POS system up and running in no time.

Where is Wix POS available?

Wix POS is currently available to users based in the U.S., Canada and U.K.-based (except Northern Ireland).
